The paper presents a framework for generating synthetic data using generative adversarial networks (GANs) for time series datasets with both continuous and discrete features. This work involves machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI), as well as data management and privacy concerns (cs.CR, cs.DB). The paper also discusses the efficacy of the proposed framework on real-world datasets, which falls under the category of experimental design and analysis (cs.SI).
